Welcome to Todos Santos!

Thank you for joining us for our computational biology and genomics workshop. Here is a summary of the topics that we are looking forward to covering over the course of the week.

Monday: Introduction to high-throughput sequencing and computational biology

  • 09:00-10:30 Introduction to Todos Santos and Group Discussion
  • 10:30-11:00 High-Throughput Sequencing Technologies
  • 11:00-12:00 UNIX and Command Line Tools
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-16:00 Manipulating and Obtaining Genomics Data
  • 16:00-17:30 Alignment and Read Mapping

Tuesday: RNA-seq

  • 09:00-12:00 RNA-seq Data Analysis I
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-17:00 RNA-seq Data Analysis II
  • 17:00-18:30 Research Presentations (with Refreshments)

Wednesday: Comparative genomic analysis

  • 09:00-14:00 Local Excursion and Lunch at Ranch in Sierra de La Laguna Natural Protected Area
  • 14:00-15:30 Assembly and Annotation
  • 15:30-17:00 Variant Calling

Thursday: Comparative genomic analysis (cont.) and Data Visualization

  • 09:00-10:30 Local BLAST and Comparative Genomics [Slides]
  • 10:30-12:00 Metagenomics and Microbial Diversity
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-13:30 Introduction to R, R Markdown, and Data Visualization [Slides]
  • 13:30-14:30 Importing and Manipulating Data in R
  • 14:30-15:15 Plotting Genomic Data with R and ggplot
  • 15:15-16:00 Figure Drawing in R
  • 16:00-17:00 Circular Representations of Genomic Data with Circos
  • 17:00-20:00 Workshop Dinner

Friday: Scripting and GitHub

  • 09:00-10:00 Code Management (GitHub)
  • 10:00-12:00 Bash Scripting
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-17:00 Introduction to Python Scripting
